Sperry Messenger serial A.S. 68533 on the fuselage side and McCook Field project number P 306 on the rudder. It is surprising that this machine still exists and is exhibited in the NASM Museum. This is a picture in color available on Flickr of this exposition machine.

[http://www.flickr.com/photos/33497395@N08/5237730530/]
